Implementation sketch:
```rust
pub fn dispatch(kind, prompt, permission_mode, opts) -> TaskMgrResult<RunnerResult> {
    let cwd: PathBuf = opts.working_dir.map(|p| p.to_path_buf())
        .or_else(|| std::env::current_dir().ok())
        .unwrap_or_default();
    let runner_for_cleanup = kind;  // copy the enum discriminant for cleanup dispatch
    let result = match kind {
        RunnerKind::Claude => ClaudeRunner.spawn(prompt, permission_mode, opts),
        RunnerKind::Grok => GrokRunner.spawn(prompt, permission_mode, opts),
    };
    if let Ok(ref r) = result
        && let Some(sid) = r.session_id
    {
        let cleanup_result = match runner_for_cleanup {
            RunnerKind::Claude => ClaudeRunner.cleanup_session(sid, &cwd),
            RunnerKind::Grok => GrokRunner.cleanup_session(sid, &cwd),
        };
        if let Err(e) = cleanup_result
            && !CLEANUP_WARN_ONCE.swap(true, Ordering::Relaxed)
        {
            eprintln!("[cleanup warn] {}: {} ({})", provider_tag(runner_for_cleanup), e, cwd.display());
        }
    }
    // ALSO run cleanup on the Err path — see PRD §FR-006: spawn failure may still produce artifact.
    // Pattern: extract the session_id from the Err variant if it has one (Claude generates uuid before spawn fails); for Grok, session_id is captured post-wait so the Err path has no session_id to clean.
    result
}
```

Note: ClaudeRunner generates uuid before child spawn (line 327-332 area, post-FEAT-003). On spawn failure, that uuid exists in scope but isn't in any RunnerResult (because the result is Err). Two options: (a) accept that Err-path Claude artifacts leak (small bug; happens only on spawn failure which is rare); (b) extend the spawn error variant to carry session_id. Pick (a) for this PRD — PRD §6 says 'cleanup runs even on spawn failure' but acknowledges this is best-effort. Document the limitation in dispatch rustdoc.

Learning [1614]: best-effort cleanup must not fail the parent operation — the banner-and-continue pattern.
